Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Is the Slovak National Party Sinking?"] </F>
  [Text] According to the FOCUS (Center for Social and 
Marketing Analysis) agency, in reply to a question on which 
parties they would vote for if parliamentary elections were held 
this weekend, respondents answered as follows: Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] (17.2 percent); Party of the 
Democratic Left (11.4 percent); Christian Democratic Movement 
(7.1 percent); and Slovak Green Party (5.0 percent). 
  The Slovak National Party (3.8 percent) would come sixth and 
the Alliance of Democrats of Slovakia, the so-called Knazkoites, 
would come eighth (2.3 percent). Only 0.4 percent of citizens 
in Slovakia would vote for the Hungarian Civic Party. More than 
20 percent of respondents would not take part in the elections 
and almost 11 percent had not yet made a decision. 

